  • Classes in elements used by elements
    Class
    Description
    Game
    Represents a chess game, including the board position, move history, and the current state of the game.
    Game.Color
    Enum representing the colors of the chess pieces.
    Move
    Represents a move in a chess game, including details such as the start and end squares, the piece moved, move notation, and the resulting position after the move.
    Player
    Represents a player in the game, which includes their color option and the color they are assigned to play.
    Player.ColorOption
    Enum representing the possible color options for a player.
    Position
    Represents the chessboard's position at any given time in the game.
    Square
    Represents a single square on the chessboard.
